(defun mon-comp-times-flt-pnt (&optional time-1 time-2)
  "Test if time TIME-1 is greater than time TIME-2.\n
Return t when TIME-1 is more recent than TIME-2.\n
When TIME-1 or TIME-2 is nil value defaults to `current-time'.\n
TIME-1 and TIME-2 are the first _two_ integers of time-value list per three integer list
of `current-time's return value e.g.:\n \(18963 22549 531000).\n
:NOTE Where third integer microsecond count \(cddr\) of `current-time' is
returned it is dropped.\n
:EXAMPLE\n\(mon-comp-times-flt-pnt 
  (current-time) ;<--TIME-1 is now!
  '(18963 22549 531000)) ;<--TIME-2 is in the past.\n ;=> t
\(mon-comp-times-flt-pnt '\(18963 22549 531000\) \(current-time\)\) ;=> nil\n
\(mon-comp-times-flt-pnt '\(18963 22549 531000\)\)\n
  \(current-time-string '\(18963 22549 531000\)\)
 ;=>\"Tue May 19 21:08:37\" ;<-- TIME-2's value converted to human speak.\n
